eft feeling unsure of why this needed to exist. (Again, this was a debut, s=
o let=E2=80=99s give her another season to convince us.)

Photo: Jonas Gustavsson/Courtesy of Ashlynn

Photo: Jonas Gustavsson/Courtesy of Ashlynn Park

Ashlynn Park, on the other hand, had no trouble convincing me at her show o=
n Friday
afternoon in the Cristina Grajales Gallery in Tribeca. Wow, what a fabulous=
 collection by someone who has paid her dues. Park did time at Yohji Yamamo=
to, Alexander Wang, and, more recently, with Simons at Calvin Klein, before=
 finally launching her own brand in 2020. Unlike everything else I saw on F=
riday, Park=E2=80=99s collection felt like it was for the O.O.C. customer, =
but without the weight of that association. I loved the sculpted knits=E2=
=80=94her signature=E2=80=94and the way she layered them. There was so
little this week that elicited desire, whereas Park=E2=80=99s ribbed wools =
and baby-doll camisoles were so good I felt compelled to mention them to ev=
ery person I could.=C2=A0

=E2=80=8A

What I=E2=80=99m Reading=E2=80=A6 and Watching=E2=80=A6
